      • loadAll

        public Map loadAll(Collection keys)
        Description copied from interface: MapDataStore
        Loads values for the provided keys if a MapLoader is configured for this map. This method never returns null. The returned map will contain deserialised keys and values.
        Specified by:
        loadAll in interface MapDataStore<K,V>
        Parameters:
        keys - the keys for which values are loaded
        Returns:
        the map from deserialised key to deserialised value
        See Also:
        MapLoader.loadAll(Collection)

      • removeAll

        public void removeAll(Collection keys)
        Removes keys from map store. It also handles Data to object conversions of keys. Directly removes keys from map store as in write-through mode. It works same for write-behind and write-through stores.
        Specified by:
        removeAll in interface MapDataStore<K,V>
        Parameters:
        keys - to be removed
